*Ealhflæd

== Holy relics ==
Oswy and his wife Eanflæd were gifted relics of several saints from Pope Vitalian around 665: Saint Peter, Saint Paul, Saint Laurentius, John the Apostle, Saint Gregory, and Saint Pancras. Eanflæd was also granted &quot;a cross, with a gold key to it, made out of the most holy chains of the apostles, Peter and Paul&quot;. This gift is documented by Bede in &quot;Ecclesiastical History of the English People&quot; as part of a returning delegation from Rome, which had been led by Wighard.

