<doc id="84181" wikidata="Q1933978" url="?curid=84181" title="Tegyrios">
<text>In Greek mythology, Tegyrios () was a King of Thrace.

== Mythology ==
Tegyrios welcomed the exiled Eumolpus and married his daughter to Eumolpus&#x27; son Ismarus. Eumolpus then planned to overthrow him. Tegyrios banished him, but later, after the death of Ismarus, Tegyrios forgave Eumolpus and pronounced him his successor.

